  "lastUpdatedOn": "2012-12-25",
  "religion": "Strait was raised a Baptist, and appears to be at least somewhat religious to this day.",
  "politicalViews": "Strait is a Republican, though notoriously quiet about his political views.",
  "author": "Tom Kershaw",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 1
    },
    {
      "parentId": 1,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "George Strait was born in Poteet, Texas and grew up in Pearsall, Texas."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 2
    },
    {
      "parentId": 2,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Strait is a quiet icon. If you're going to get him talking, the conversation will likely revolve around his music. However, we know he was raised a Baptist.",
      "sourceTitle": "George Strait",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.nndb.com/people/225/000025150/"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "text": "He did have a religious upbringing, to which he credits his father:",
      "parentId": 2
    },
    {
      "type": "quote",
      "id": 3
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 4,
      "parentId": 3
    },
    {
      "parentId": 4,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "My dad, of course, raised my brother and me on his own, and he raised us in a real religious atmosphere. We're all Baptists, and he always told me that the Lord would tell me what He wanted me to do with my life; and I kind of believe that's really true. So I didn't worry about it much, didn't think about it that much.",
      "sourceTitle": "George Strait – Updated page 8",
      "sourceUrl": "http://books.google.com/books?id=k3ze2mnY6icC&pg=PA8&lpg=PA8&dq=George+Strait+religion&source=bl&ots=NNYE8_w8C7&sig=TDF2i0lyCbRLguJJGa2Oh8KmbsI&hl=en&sa=X&ei=lhTGULjRJIXliALdy4CoBw&ved=0CEgQ6AEwAw#v=onepage&q=George%20Strait%20religion&f=false"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 5
    },
    {
      "parentId": 5,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Strait eloped with his high school sweetheart in Mexico, but when they returned to Texas, they had a ceremony in a church.",
      "sourceTitle": "George and Norma Celebrate 40 Years Together",
      "sourceUrl": "http://kilt.cbslocal.com/2011/11/29/george-and-norma-celebrate-40-years-together/"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Which church is unclear.",
      "parentId": 5
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 6
    },
    {
      "parentId": 6,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "And like most country music stars, he's got a few religious-themed songs in his repertoire, such as \"I Saw God Today,\" with lyrics like:"
    },
    {
      "type": "quote",
      "id": 7
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 8,
      "parentId": 7
    },
    {
      "parentId": 8,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "I've been to church/I've read the book/I know He's there/But I don't look/near as often as I should/His fingerprints are everywhere/I just look down and stop and stare/open my eyes and then I swear/I Saw God Today.",
      "sourceTitle": "I Saw God Today Lyrics – George Strait",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.sing365.com/music/lyric.nsf/I-Saw-God-Today-lyrics-George-Strait/EF866273A3FFA0DA482573FB000EED82"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 9
    },
    {
      "parentId": 9,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "So, despite the fact that Strait doesn't talk about it, we can say with considerable confidence that he's at least somewhat religious, and probably still a Baptist."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "id": 10
    },
    {
      "parentId": 10,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Strait talking politics"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 11
    },
    {
      "parentId": 11,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "It won't happen, folks. In the arena of politics, Strait is even more tight-lipped than he is with his religious views. In 2012, Republican presidential candidate Newt Gingrich used his song, \"Heartland,\" at campaign events–which obviously Strait didn't take issue with.",
      "sourceTitle": "Gingrich, Strait, McBride and country music in campaigns",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.countrystandardtime.com/blog/rootstootshoots/entry.asp?xid=843"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "text": "But when asked to comment about candidates, issues, or anything political for that matter, all reporters could get was a statement from Strait's publicist:",
      "parentId": 11
    },
    {
      "type": "quote",
      "id": 12
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 13,
      "parentId": 12
    },
    {
      "parentId": 13,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "George never comments publicly on political views.",
      "sourceTitle": "Gingrich, Strait, McBride and country music in campaigns",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.countrystandardtime.com/blog/rootstootshoots/entry.asp?xid=843"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 14
    },
    {
      "parentId": 14,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "OK then…"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 15
    },
    {
      "parentId": 15,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "We have one tiny piece of evidence that suggests that Strait is probably a Republican. In 1992, he donated $240 to the National Republican Senatorial Committee.",
      "sourceTitle": "George Strait's Federal Campaign Contribution Report",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.newsmeat.com/celebrity_political_donations/George_Strait.php"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 16
    },
    {
      "parentId": 16,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Beyond that, plenty of fan sites and rumor mills speculate that he's a Republican,",
      "sourceTitle": "List of Republican celebrities",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.freerepublic.com/focus/chat/1311976/posts"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "text": "so there must be some reason for that, which might just be he's a country singer from Texas.",
      "parentId": 16
    }
  ],
